---
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout title="Jenny K Walsh — Return Customer Dashboard">
  <div class="case-study">

    <div class="case-study-header">
      <p class="label">1-800 Contacts &nbsp;·&nbsp; Case study</p>
      <h1>Return Customer Dashboard</h1>
      <p class="role">Staff Product Designer</p>
    </div>

    <div class="hero-image">
      <img src="/work/return-customer-dashboard/hero.webp" alt="Return Customer Dashboard" />
    </div>

    <div class="content">

      <section class="intro">
        <p>1-800 Contacts earns a significant portion of their revenue from repeat customers, but the online experience was never built with them in mind. Prescription data was stored in their accounts, a major reason they came back, yet every session dropped them into a first-time buyer flow, with friction and confusion instead of the streamlined experience they deserved. I set out to fix that by designing a dashboard that would turn reordering contact lenses into a fast, one-click process.</p>
      </section>

      <section class="section">
        <h2>The problem</h2>
        <div class="section-body">
          <p>Repeat customers had to navigate an order flow built for first-time buyers. There was no easy access to existing prescriptions, previous orders, or account information.</p>
          <p>When a returning customer signed in, they were dropped straight into a new customer order flow with no context. This created duplicate accounts, drove up service calls, lowered conversion rates, and caused widespread confusion.</p>
          <p>In user sessions, we watched customers log in and wander through account pages trying to find what they needed, usually a way to update their prescription or reorder their last purchase. Call center agents confirmed the same thing: customers were calling in confused about how to place a reorder.</p>
          <p>The existing experience auto-loaded a pre-filled cart after login with no explanation. It was disorienting, confusing, and wasn't converting well. Customers who did manage to order had to fight through the experience to get there.</p>
        </div>
      </section>

      <section class="section">
        <h2>My proposed solution</h2>
        <div class="section-body">
          <p>A Return Customer Dashboard that gives returning customers a smooth reorder flow and easy access to their prescription and account information.</p>
          <p>I designed a personalized experience using existing customer data to anticipate what each person was most likely looking for and surface it immediately. The architecture supported alerts, flexible slots for personalized components from our customer data platform, and space for promotional messaging. I also carved out a spot for a bit of personality with the brand mascot, Seemore the Eye Guy.</p>
          <div class="image-break">
            <img src="/work/return-customer-dashboard/wireframe.webp" alt="" />
          </div>
        </div>
      </section>

    </div>

    <div class="phone-carousel">
      <img src="/work/return-customer-dashboard/phone1.webp" alt="" />
      <img src="/work/return-customer-dashboard/phone2.webp" alt="" />
      <img src="/work/return-customer-dashboard/phone3.webp" alt="" />
      <img src="/work/return-customer-dashboard/phone4.webp" alt="" />
      <img src="/work/return-customer-dashboard/phone5.png" alt="" />
      <img src="/work/return-customer-dashboard/phone6.webp" alt="" />
    </div>

    <div class="content">

      <section class="section">
        <h2>My approach</h2>
        <div class="section-body">
          <p>I leaned heavily into qualitative user testing during the MVP phase, which gave me a strong foundation to design from. As the product matured, I layered in quantitative A/B testing to make targeted improvements across iterations.</p>
          <p>I worked closely with engineering throughout, constantly syncing on how to meet requirements, manage scope, and keep design and development quality high. I also spent time with our data analysts to understand how we'd measure success and uncover edge cases the team might have missed.</p>
          <p>Before sketching anything, I mapped out the full range of customer states our data could support. What do we know about someone who ordered this week? Someone who hasn't ordered in two years? A subscription customer? Someone who registered but never purchased? The personalization possibilities were complex and fascinating.</p>
          <p>After that analysis, we scoped the MVP down to the top five customer states: ready to reorder (featuring most recent product and prescription), recent order, shipped order, subscription, and abandoned cart. After multiple prototype iterations and moderated user testing, we launched the MVP as an A/B test to 50% of our customer base.</p>
        </div>
      </section>

    <div class="content content-lower">

      <section class="section outcome">
        <h2>Outcome</h2>
        <div class="section-body">
          <div class="stats">
            <div class="stat">
              <span class="stat-number">+2%</span>
              <span class="stat-label">Conversion uplift</span>
            </div>
            <div class="stat">
              <span class="stat-number">+3%</span>
              <span class="stat-label">Revenue per visitor</span>
            </div>
            <div class="stat">
              <span class="stat-number">$2.3MM</span>
              <span class="stat-label">Annual revenue boost</span>
            </div>
          </div>
          <p>The MVP delivered a 2% conversion uplift and a 3% increase in revenue per visitor, translating to a $2.3 million annual revenue boost. We saw a positive response from customers within the first three weeks. The project also laid the groundwork for future personalization efforts and CMS-driven marketing campaigns.</p>
        </div>
      </section>

      <div class="image-break">
        <img src="/work/return-customer-dashboard/ipad.webp" alt="" />
      </div>

      <div class="back-link">
        <a href="/work">← All work</a>
      </div>

    </div>
  </div>
</Layout>

<style>
  .case-study {
    padding-bottom: 8rem;
    overflow-x: hidden;
  }

  .case-study-header {
    padding: 180px 3rem 3rem;
    max-width: 1200px;
  }

  .label {
    font-size: 0.85rem;
    font-weight: 700;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    letter-spacing: 0.08em;
    color: var(--black);
    margin-bottom: 0.35rem;
  }

  h1 {
    font-size: clamp(2.5rem, 6vw, 5rem);
    font-weight: 900;
    line-height: 1.05;
    margin: 1rem 0;
  }

  .role {
    display: inline-block;
    font-size: 0.85rem;
    font-weight: 700;
    color: var(--white);
    background: var(--black);
    padding: 0.3rem 0.75rem;
  }

  .hero-image {
    width: 100%;
  }

  .hero-image img {
    width: 100%;
    height: auto;
    display: block;
  }

  .content {
    max-width: 1200px;
    padding: 0;
    margin: 0 auto;
  }

  .intro {
    padding: 4rem 3rem;
  }

  .intro p {
    font-size: clamp(1.15rem, 2vw, 1.4rem);
    line-height: 1.75;
    font-weight: 300;
  }

  .section {
    padding: 4rem 3rem;
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 280px 1fr;
    gap: 4rem;
    border-top: 1px solid rgba(0,0,0,0.1);
  }

  h2 {
    font-size: 1.4rem;
    font-weight: 900;
    line-height: 1.2;
    padding-top: 0.25rem;
  }

  .section-body {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 1.25rem;
    font-size: 1.1rem;
    line-height: 1.8;
  }

  .image-break {
    margin: 1rem 0 0;
  }

  .image-break img {
    width: 100%;
    height: auto;
    display: block;
    border-radius: 4px;
  }

  .image-break.two-up {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr;
    gap: 1rem;
  }

  .phone-carousel {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: row;
    gap: 15px;
    padding: 1rem 20px 3rem;
  }

  .phone-carousel img {
    flex: 1 1 0;
    width: 0;
    height: auto;
    display: block;
  }

  .outcome {
    background: var(--black);
    color: var(--white);
    padding: 4rem 3rem;
    border-radius: 4px;
    border-top: none;
    grid-template-columns: 1fr;
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 2rem;
    margin: 0.5rem 0 2rem;
  }

  .outcome h2 {
    color: #F6FF00;
  }

  .outcome .section-body {
    gap: 1.5rem;
  }

  .stats {
    display: flex;
    gap: 4rem;
    padding-bottom: 1rem;
    border-bottom: 1px solid rgba(255,255,255,0.15);
  }

  .stat {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 0.25rem;
  }

  .stat-number {
    font-size: clamp(2rem, 4vw, 3rem);
    font-weight: 900;
    color: #F6FF00;
    line-height: 1;
  }

  .stat-label {
    font-size: 0.85rem;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    letter-spacing: 0.08em;
    opacity: 0.6;
  }

  .back-link {
    padding: 4rem 3rem 0;
    border-top: 1px solid rgba(0,0,0,0.1);
  }

  .back-link a {
    font-size: 1rem;
    font-weight: 700;
    color: var(--black);
    text-decoration: none;
    background-color: #F6FF00;
    padding: 0 4px;
    display: inline-block;
    transition: box-shadow 0.1s steps(2), transform 0.1s steps(2);
  }

  .back-link a:hover {
    transform: translateY(-2px);
    box-shadow: 4px 2px 0 #00FFFF, -4px -2px 0 #FF00FF;
  }


  @media (max-width: 768px) {
    .case-study-header {
      padding: 160px 1.5rem 2rem;
    }

    .content {
      padding: 0 1.5rem;
    }

    .intro {
      padding: 2rem 0;
    }

    .section {
      grid-template-columns: 1fr;
      gap: 1.5rem;
      padding: 2rem 0;
    }

    .back-link {
      padding: 2rem 0 0;
    }

    .image-break.two-up,
    .image-break.four-up {
      grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr;
    }

    .content-lower {
      padding-left: 0;
      padding-right: 0;
    }

    .outcome {
      padding: 2rem;
    }

    .stats {
      flex-direction: column;
      gap: 2rem;
    }

    .phone-carousel {
      overflow-x: scroll;
      scroll-snap-type: x mandatory;
      -webkit-overflow-scrolling: touch;
      gap: 12px;
      padding: 1rem 0 0.5rem;
      margin: 0;
    }

    .phone-carousel img {
      width: 82vw;
      flex: none;
      scroll-snap-align: center;
      border-radius: 8px;
    }

    .phone-carousel img:first-child {
      margin-left: calc(50vw - 41vw);
    }

    .phone-carousel img:last-child {
      margin-right: calc(50vw - 41vw);
    }

  }
</style>


